Notes: Environmental Tolerances: Does very poorly under low-N conditions like most grasses.
Soil Drainage: ["Moderately well drained","Well drained","Excessively drained","Well drained muck"]
Planting green: Utilizing a roller-crimper is suggested when planting corn into material greater than 12" tall as un-rolled cover may impact emergence.
Notes: Failure to overwinter reliably in USDA hardiness zones 5 and colder means biomass production may be low, which potentially limits grazing/forage harvest value.
